---
import PortalLayout from '../layouts/PortalLayout.astro'
---

<PortalLayout
  title="About — Sohma Institute"
  description="A Registered Training Organisation headquartered in Cairns, specialising in tropical and Indigenous medicine. Node III of the Regenerative Health Ecology."
>
  <article class="about-page">

    <!-- HERO -->
    <header class="about-hero">
      <div class="section-label">About the Institute</div>
      <h1 class="hero-title">A training institution built for the medicine <span class="hero-accent">that already exists.</span></h1>
      <p class="hero-lead">The Sohma Institute of Traditional Medicines is a Registered Training Organisation headquartered in Cairns, Far North Queensland. It exists because no institution in Australia is training practitioners to work with traditional pharmacological systems at the level of complexity those systems actually operate at.</p>
    </header>


    <!-- SECTION 1: THE INSTITUTION -->
    <section class="institution-section" id="institution">
      <h2 class="section-heading">The Institution</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">If you had thirty seconds to explain what this place is — here it is.</p>

      <div class="institution-grid">
        <div class="institution-card">
          <div class="institution-label">Institutional Class</div>
          <h3>Registered Training Organisation</h3>
          <p>An Australian RTO operating under the National Vocational Education and Training Regulator Act. Authorised to deliver nationally recognised qualifications in traditional and integrative medicine.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="institution-card">
          <div class="institution-label">Jurisdictional Anchor</div>
          <h3>Cairns, Far North Queensland</h3>
          <p>Headquartered in tropical Australia — the continent's highest concentration of Indigenous pharmacopoeia, endemic medicinal species, and unbroken traditional knowledge transmission. The location is the curriculum.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="institution-card">
          <div class="institution-label">Specialisation</div>
          <h3>Tropical & Indigenous Medicine</h3>
          <p>Five academic divisions covering complex herbal medicines, emergent and entheogenic modalities, systems medicine, environmental and nutritional medicine, and lifestyle therapeutics. Each division operates its own research and credentialing pipeline.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="institution-card">
          <div class="institution-label">What Makes It Different</div>
          <h3>Post-Reductionist Pedagogy</h3>
          <p>Every other provider in Australia teaches traditional medicine through a biomedical reduction filter. The Institute teaches it as a sophisticated therapeutic architecture in its own right — then maps it to modern systems biology, not the other way around.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- SECTION 2: POSITION WITHIN THE ECOLOGY -->
    <section class="ecology-section" id="ecology">
      <h2 class="section-heading">Position Within the Regenerative Health Ecology</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">The Institute doesn't operate in isolation. It's Node III of a four-part ecology — receiving clinical intelligence from the front line and distributing validated knowledge outward. This is the only page on the site where the bigger picture is made explicit.</p>

      <!-- Ecology Diagram -->
      <div class="ecology-diagram">
        <div class="ecology-node" data-accent="warm">
          <div class="ecology-node-num">I</div>
          <div class="ecology-node-body">
            <h3>Sohma House</h3>
            <span class="ecology-node-role">Clinical Core</span>
            <p>Multi-disciplinary clinic. Source of patient data, clinical training sites, research participants, and real-world outcome data.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="ecology-flow">
          <div class="ecology-flow-line"></div>
          <div class="ecology-flow-labels">
            <span class="flow-in">Patient data, training sites, research participants</span>
            <span class="flow-out">Validated protocols, credentialed practitioners</span>
          </div>
          <div class="ecology-flow-line"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="ecology-node active" data-accent="terracotta">
          <div class="ecology-node-num">III</div>
          <div class="ecology-node-body">
            <h3>Sohma Institute</h3>
            <span class="ecology-node-role">Education, Research & Credentialing</span>
            <p>Transforms clinical intelligence into structured knowledge. Trains practitioners. Validates protocols. Publishes research. You are here.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="ecology-flow">
          <div class="ecology-flow-line"></div>
          <div class="ecology-flow-labels">
            <span class="flow-in">Research findings, credentialing frameworks</span>
            <span class="flow-out">Regulatory advisory, policy consulting, curriculum licensing</span>
          </div>
          <div class="ecology-flow-line"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="ecology-node" data-accent="green">
          <div class="ecology-node-num">IV</div>
          <div class="ecology-node-body">
            <h3>Consulting Arm</h3>
            <span class="ecology-node-role">Advisory & Dissemination</span>
            <p>Regulatory consulting, policy advisory, curriculum consulting for external providers. The commercial translation of Institute research and credentialing.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ecology-note">
        <p><strong>The loop is closed by design.</strong> Clinical data flows into research. Research produces validated protocols. Protocols are distributed through education and the practitioner network. Practitioners generate new clinical data. Every node feeds every other node.</p>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- SECTION 3: GOVERNANCE & ACCREDITATION -->
    <section class="governance-section" id="governance">
      <h2 class="section-heading">Governance & Accreditation</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">Three oversight bodies govern the Institute's academic, clinical, and cultural integrity. Each operates with constitutional authority — not advisory capacity.</p>

      <div class="governance-grid">
        <div class="governance-card">
          <div class="governance-icon">
            <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M2 3h6a4 4 0 0 1 4 4v14a3 3 0 0 0-3-3H2z"/><path d="M22 3h-6a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v14a3 3 0 0 1 3-3h7z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Academic Board</h3>
          <p>Oversees curriculum, credentialing standards, and research ethics. Membership drawn from Institute Fellows, external academics, and community representatives.</p>
          <div class="governance-detail">Indigenous representation is constitutionally mandated.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="governance-card">
          <div class="governance-icon">
            <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M22 12h-4l-3 9L9 3l-3 9H2"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Clinical Standards Committee</h3>
          <p>Governs protocol standards, practitioner competency, and adverse event reporting. Membership drawn from active clinical practitioners.</p>
          <div class="governance-detail">Responsible for protocol tier classification (A / B / C).</div>
        </div>
        <div class="governance-card">
          <div class="governance-icon">
            <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M2 12h20"/><path d="M12 2a15.3 15.3 0 0 1 4 10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1-4 10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1-4-10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1 4-10z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Indigenous Advisory Council</h3>
          <p>Holds veto authority over any research, curriculum, or publication involving Indigenous knowledge systems. Operates under Indigenous Data Sovereignty with independent legal counsel.</p>
          <div class="governance-detail">Not advisory. Constitutional authority with veto power.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Accreditation Pathway -->
      <div class="accreditation-section">
        <h3 class="accreditation-heading">Accreditation Pathway</h3>
        <div class="accreditation-pathway">
          <div class="accreditation-step">
            <div class="accreditation-badge">ASQA</div>
            <span>RTO Registration</span>
            <p>National Vocational Education and Training Regulator</p>
          </div>
          <div class="accreditation-arrow">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div class="accreditation-step">
            <div class="accreditation-badge">TEQSA</div>
            <span>University Articulation</span>
            <p>Partner articulation agreements for higher education pathways</p>
          </div>
          <div class="accreditation-arrow">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div class="accreditation-step">
            <div class="accreditation-badge">TGA</div>
            <span>Research Compliance</span>
            <p>NHMRC guidelines, institutional ethics, clinical trial compliance</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="about-cta">
      <div class="about-cta-inner">
        <h2>Questions about the Institute?</h2>
        <p>If you're a practitioner, researcher, or potential partner — get in touch.</p>
        <a href="/contact" class="cta-primary">Contact Us</a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </article>
</PortalLayout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    font-family: 'Manrope', sans-serif;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    padding: 0;
  }
  .about-page p { line-height: 1.8; margin: 0 0 1rem; }
  .about-page p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .about-page h2, .about-page h3 { margin: 0; }

  /* ═══════════ HERO ═══════════ */
  .about-hero {
    padding: 6rem 0 5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light);
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .section-label {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    font-family: 'Manrope', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    color: var(--accent-dark);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .section-label::after {
    content: '';
    flex: 1;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--accent-line);
  }

  .hero-title {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5vw, 3.25rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.0;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 0 2rem;
    padding-left: 2rem;
  }

  .hero-accent {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--accent-dark);
  }

  .hero-lead {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--text-body-65);
    line-height: 1.85;
    max-width: 600px;
    padding-left: 2rem;
  }


  /* ═══════════ SECTION HEADINGS ═══════════ */
  .about-page .section-heading {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }

  .about-page .section-intro {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-body-55);
    line-height: 1.8;
    max-width: 640px;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }


  /* ═══════════ SECTION 1: THE INSTITUTION ═══════════ */
  .institution-section {
    padding-bottom: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light);
  }

  .institution-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .institution-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--border-light);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1.75rem;
    transition: border-color 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
  }

  .institution-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent-border-15);
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px var(--bg-card);
  }

  .institution-label {
    font-size: 0.625rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--accent-dark);
    opacity: 0.7;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .institution-card h3 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .institution-card p {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--text-body-60);
    line-height: 1.75;
  }


  /* ═══════════ SECTION 2: ECOLOGY ═══════════ */
  .ecology-section {
    padding-bottom: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light);
  }

  .ecology-diagram {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto 2rem;
  }

  .ecology-node {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    padding: 1.75rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-light);
    border-radius: 6px;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .ecology-node.active {
    border-color: var(--accent-border-25);
    background: var(--accent-bg-02);
  }

  .ecology-node-num {
    width: 36px;
    height: 36px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  [data-accent="warm"] .ecology-node-num {
    color: var(--chart-warm);
    border: 2px solid var(--chart-warm);
  }

  [data-accent="terracotta"] .ecology-node-num {
    color: var(--accent-dark);
    border: 2px solid var(--accent-dark);
  }

  [data-accent="green"] .ecology-node-num {
    color: var(--accent-green);
    border: 2px solid var(--accent-green);
  }

  .ecology-node-body h3 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .ecology-node-role {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.625rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .ecology-node-body p {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--text-body-60);
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .ecology-flow {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1.75rem 0 1.75rem 18px;
  }

  .ecology-flow-line {
    width: 2px;
    height: 36px;
    background: var(--border-medium);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .ecology-flow-labels {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.25rem;
    flex: 1;
  }

  .flow-in, .flow-out {
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
  }

  .flow-in::before {
    content: '↓ ';
    color: var(--accent-green);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .flow-out::before {
    content: '↑ ';
    color: var(--accent-dark);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .ecology-note {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-light);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .ecology-note p {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--text-body-60);
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .ecology-note strong {
    color: var(--text-heading);
  }


  /* ═══════════ SECTION 3: GOVERNANCE ═══════════ */
  .governance-section {
    padding-bottom: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light);
  }

  .governance-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .governance-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--border-light);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1.75rem;
    transition: border-color 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
  }

  .governance-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent-border-15);
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px var(--bg-card);
  }

  .governance-icon {
    color: var(--accent-dark);
    opacity: 0.6;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .governance-card h3 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .governance-card p {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--text-body-60);
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .governance-detail {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--accent-dark);
    opacity: 0.7;
  }


  /* ═══════════ ACCREDITATION PATHWAY ═══════════ */
  .accreditation-section {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .accreditation-heading {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .accreditation-pathway {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .accreditation-step {
    flex: 1;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 1.25rem 1rem;
  }

  .accreditation-badge {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 52px;
    height: 52px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    border: 2px solid var(--accent-dark);
    font-family: 'Manrope', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--accent-dark);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .accreditation-step span {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 0.375rem;
  }

  .accreditation-step p {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text-body-50);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .accreditation-arrow {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }


  /* ═══════════ CTA ═══════════ */
  .about-cta {
    padding: 3rem 0 4rem;
  }

  .about-cta-inner {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--bg-dark-start) 0%, var(--bg-dark-end) 100%);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 2.5rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .about-cta-inner h2 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--text-on-dark);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .about-cta-inner p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: rgba(240,235,229,0.5);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .cta-primary {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--accent-dark);
    color: var(--bg-surface);
    font-family: 'Manrope', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    padding: 12px 28px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.2s;
  }

  .cta-primary:hover {
    background: var(--accent-darker-hover);
  }


  /* ═══════════ RESPONSIVE ═══════════ */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .institution-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .governance-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .accreditation-pathway {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
    }

    .accreditation-arrow {
      transform: rotate(90deg);
      padding-top: 0;
    }

    .ecology-node {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.75rem;
    }

    .ecology-flow {
      padding-left: 36px;
    }
  }
</style>
